'''Cruzeiro Brasil''' is a cross-platform [[world]] with a cruise ship theme, created by Bia_Kawaii_Br. Released in 2021, it is one of the most popular worlds for Brazilians to meet and socialize.

[[File:Cruzeiro entrance.png|thumb|This is the entrance to Cruzeiro Brasil.]]

==Design==
The world is designed as a massive cruise ship named Akagi, inspired by an aircraft carrier from the Imperial Japanese Navy. The ship sails across the entirety of the Amazonian Blue, starting in Rio Grande do Sul and traveling up to Amapá, before crossing the Atlantic Ocean to dock at Praia do Campeche in Florianópolis. The world features various themed areas, ranging from Brazilian memes and popular Brazilian, game areas, to private spaces, and more. Seasonal updates are released at specific times of the year, and the world includes a day-night cycle. There are also various interactive items, such as pens and drivable cars.

==Map overview==
'''Realistic design and diverse spaces:'''

*'''Decks and pools:''' The outdoor decks offer spaces where users can relax by the pools, socialize, and enjoy views of a simulated ocean. The attention to detail aims to create a realistic cruise experience.

*'''Private cabins:''' The map includes private rooms modeled after real cruise ship cabins, providing spaces where users can "rest" their avatars. Each cabin is uniquely decorated to enhance the sense of immersion.

*'''Entertainment areas:''' These include bars, a nightclub, karaoke rooms, and a game room, all of which are frequently used for community-hosted parties and events.

'''Interactive features:'''

*'''Functional games:''' The map includes various mini-games that users can play while exploring the cruise, such as card games and board games adapted for the virtual environment.

*'''Events and role-playing:''' The community frequently organizes themed events, parties, and role-playing sessions, utilizing different areas of the map, such as the '''Podcast Room''' and '''School''' for more specific interactions.

'''Specialized areas:'''

*'''Hospital:''' This area allows players to role-play emergency situations or simply explore a medical environment.

*'''Church:''' This space can be used for ceremonies, religious gatherings, or quiet reflection.

